column2532: Now you're going to do a questionnaire by yourself, or you can have your (mom/dad) come in to help you.  I'm going to explain the questionnaire first and then leave the room.  Whenever you're done answering all the questions, come outside to let me know.    All (boys/girls) change and develop physically, mentally, and emotionally in the process of 'growing up.'  The growth and development of your body is an especially important part of this process of becoming a grown-up.  Since it is normal for different (boys/girls) to go through these physical changes at different times, we are interested in learning about what changes are usually happening in (boys/girls) when they are your age. We would like to ask you to help us get this information by answering some questions about how you are currently growing and developing.    What is the child's sex?    Do your best to answer carefully. If you do not understand a question or do not know the answer, just choose 'I don't know.'      To answer the questions, click on the answer that's true for you.  You may also need to type answers into a text box or click on a button.  If you're not sure how to answer, come outside to let me know, and I'll have your (mom/dad) help you.     If you have not already done so, you can take off the heart monitor after I leave the room, and you can leave it on the table.
